<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionIRI> <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/2026-07-18> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "RockWorx Aerospace" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "A BFO/CCO-conformant ontology of the U.S. DoD acquisition lifecycle in four modules: the base (DoDI 5000.85 Major Capability Acquisition -- what IS law/policy), the transformation overlay (the 2025 Warfighting Acquisition System / Joint Force Requirements Process reform), the legislative-horizon layer (what MIGHT become law -- pending bills as non-asserted candidate changes), and the SysML v2 link bridge. Creator: RockWorx Aerospace. License: BSD-3-Clause." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/license> <https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "RockWorx Acquisition Ontology" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "RockWorx Acquisition Ontology" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "2026-07-18" .
