# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#changeType
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#changeType> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#changeType> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "What the proposal would do to the referenced construct if enacted: ADD | MODIFY | SUPERSEDE." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#changeType> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "change type" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#changeType> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "What the proposal would do to the referenced construct if enacted: ADD | MODIFY | SUPERSEDE." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#enactmentLikelihood
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#enactmentLikelihood> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#enactmentLikelihood> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "An explicit, sourced JUDGMENT of the likelihood the proposal is enacted: LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH. This is a judgment, NEVER a fact; it is an annotation and is invisible to the reasoner. It must always be paired with a likelihoodBasis." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#enactmentLikelihood> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "enactment likelihood" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#enactmentLikelihood> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An explicit, sourced judgment (LOW | MEDIUM | HIGH) of the likelihood of enactment; a judgment, never a fact." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#graduatedTo
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#graduatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#graduatedTo> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "On enactment, points a (now owl:deprecated) legislative candidate change to the base/transform construct that received the enacted change through the governed, append-only graduation migration." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#graduatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "graduated to" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#graduatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Points an enacted, graduated candidate change to the base/transform construct that received the change." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#impactAssessment
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#impactAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#impactAssessment> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The analytic narrative of the downstream effect the proposal would have on the acquisition process if enacted -- the product of the horizon layer." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#impactAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "impact assessment" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#impactAssessment> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The analytic narrative of the downstream effect the proposal would have if enacted." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#legislativeMaturity
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#legislativeMaturity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#legislativeMaturity> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The rung a legislative candidate change occupies on the legislative-maturity ladder, taken from the Congress.gov API's real status: one of proposed | introduced | reported | passed-one-chamber | in-conference | enacted. On 'enacted' the candidate graduates out of the horizon into transform/base with statutory provenance." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#legislativeMaturity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "legislative maturity" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#legislativeMaturity> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The legislative-maturity rung (proposed | introduced | reported | passed-one-chamber | in-conference | enacted), taken from the source's real status." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#likelihoodBasis
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#likelihoodBasis> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#likelihoodBasis> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The sourced rationale for an enactmentLikelihood judgment; a likelihood is never a bare value." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#likelihoodBasis> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "likelihood basis" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#likelihoodBasis> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The sourced rationale for an enactmentLikelihood judgment." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#prospectiveAuthorityTier
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#prospectiveAuthorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#prospectiveAuthorityTier> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The authority tier a legislative candidate change WOULD establish if enacted -- e.g. STATUTE-PENDING (a pending statute). This is a horizon-layer annotation about a proposal; it is distinct from the transform layer's rwxt:authorityTier, which records the ASSERTED authority basis of an in-effect construct. Keeping them separate preserves the prospective-vs-asserted boundary. On enactment the construct gains rwxt:authorityTier via the graduation migration, not this property." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#prospectiveAuthorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "prospective authority tier" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#prospectiveAuthorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The authority tier a legislative candidate change would establish if enacted (e.g. STATUTE-PENDING); distinct from the transform layer's asserted authorityTier." .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AnnotationProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "The level of authority -- STATUTE > POLICY > GUIDANCE -- from which an acquisition construct is derived." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "authority tier" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/transform#authorityTier> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The level of authority -- STATUTE > POLICY > GUIDANCE -- from which an acquisition construct is derived." .
