<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#wouldAffect> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#wouldAffect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#LegislativeCandidateChange> .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#wouldAffect> <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> "Relates a legislative candidate change to the existing base or transform construct it would ADD to, MODIFY, or SUPERSEDE if the proposal were enacted. This is an INTENSIONAL reference for analysis only: it asserts NO change to the referenced construct. It is deliberately NOT a subproperty of any base relation and carries no range axiom, so a reasoner infers nothing about the referenced construct. The target construct is referenced by its class IRI via OWL 2 punning (a class name used as an individual)." .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#wouldAffect> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "would affect" .
<https://w3id.org/rockworx/acq/horizon#wouldAffect> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Relates a legislative candidate change to the base/transform construct it would add to, modify, or supersede if enacted; an intensional reference that asserts no change to the target." .
